  z$flush_delayed = FALSE;
  assert(!(x == 2 && y == 2 && z == 2));

{

  /* Program was expected to be safe for X86, model checker should have said NO.
This likely is a bug in the tool chain. */

  /* Program was expected to be safe for X86, model checker should have said NO.
This likely is a bug in the tool chain. */
  z = nondet_int();
  /* Program was expected to be safe for X86, model checker should have said NO.
This likely is a bug in the tool chain. */

  __VERIFIER_atomic_end();
  /* Program was expected to be safe for X86, model checker should have said NO.
This likely is a bug in the tool chain. */
  assert(!(x == 2 && y == 2 && z == 2));
  return 0;
}

  __global_lock=1; 
  return;
